Class GameObject

java.lang.Object
GameEngine.GameObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
AISnakeController, DynamicObstacle, FoodCircle, GameManager, GameMap, GameoverOverlay, GameplayOverlay, HighscoresOverlay, InputSnakeController, Snake, SnakeController, StaticObstacle, TextOverlay, Unit
public class GameObject extends Object
Represents an object of a game. This class is made to be inherited.

    • setScene

      protected final void setScene(Scene scene, int id) throws GameEngineException
      Sets the game object's to the scene it's contained in Should only be called by a scene
      Parameters:
      scene - the scene the game object is in
      id - the unique (within the scene) id for the object
      Throws:
      GameEngineException - if the game object is already in a scene

    • detachScene

      protected final void detachScene()
      Detaches the game object of it's scene. Doesn't do anything if the game object isn't in a scene. Should only be called by Scene.

      public void start()
      Called when the game engine starts or whenever the object is added to a scene, in case the game engine is already running

    • stop

      public void stop()
      Called when the game engine stops. or whenever the object is removed from a scene, in the case the game engine is running
